posts.subject: 60 minutes May 3, 2020 The tragedy of income loss.
posts.body:
Who wouldn't sympathize with their plight?

That is, until you get to the part where they own $300,000 in federal student loans.

Now I do understand that there is a whole class of lizardpeople dedicated to turning citizens into slaves - especially within the ed biz. But just what is the chump's culpability here? Do they get a free get out of jail card at public expense - because poor them? They really didn't grasp the reality of this debt they took on? And now many oh so righteous people think "rest of us" should bail them out? Believe the Bernie Bros even expect a full rescue.

Fuck that.

I never asked for these federal programs, and they were sold to the public as being "risk free". No matter where these borrowers went - they could not hide. So making these loans was cost free to the public.

That's the way the federal student loan program was sold.

But as it turns out, these loans were just another way to turn citizens into slaves. This time - for a good cause. Supporting overpaid college administrators and staff. And alas, many of these loans went to the truly stupid. Those who wouldn't blink at the prospect of $300K debts.

So cry me a river. You stupid do-gooders own this. And now the beneficiaries of this public largess just need to sell organs.

Tell me, do you believe that student loans represent ALL this woman's debt? Or are the real estate industries, the credit card companies, and the automotive industry into her too?

"Rest of us" have no interest in emancipating this one. She really was too stupid to breed.

And BTW. "Iron deficiencies" are often a made up disability. They send doctors to Hawaii to practice selling that con. Only 60 minutes could find unworthies of this caliber.......

Ever stop to consider how much this specimen cost her health insurance risk group? With all her likely unneeded bullshit? Would you wish to be in the same risk pool as this individual?

>>7446f77d-1680-4c78-8df4-abbd3408c37d

Zeronet needs a simpler configuration model. Perhaps a simple slider.

You can take some fairly powerful hardware and bring it to a crawl if you fail to get that config file right. Should not be this sensitive or hard to configure - but it is.

Properly configuired - Zeronet flies. It transfers files very rapidly. Improperly configured? It just wallows.

Never forget that we're flying a beta here. Vers 1.0 is not yet.

posts.subject: Deactivated an ancient Reddit account after thorough wiping.
posts.body:
Felt good.

That Firefox addon "Nuke Reddit History" was a big help, but you must keep doing it over and over again until nothing is left. Multiple browser closing/reopenings may be required.

Slowly finishing up Google too. Am done with them. NOTHING is better than these censoring platforms, and no one should tolerate even the slightest moderation.

Such principles were once so obvious, but now this seems such a long time ago. This nation's spirit has lost something. I hope it comes back.
